{
  "stem": "7744.2",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 9.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "What happened, though, is that I was advised, because I was sick in that-- at that time, that to go to Israel for me was not a good idea.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "And that's where I wanted to go, because most of the kids went to Israel.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "They had no one, and they had no one in Canada, no one in the States, and-- and Israel, of course, was the haven.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "So most of them went to Israel, and I was terribly upset that I wasn't supposed to go to Israel.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "But my aunt was very anxious for me to come to Canada.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "And as I said, in 1948, I came to Canada on a false x-ray, which simply means that the x-ray that was produced for my exit was not my own, and it was a clear x-ray.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "That does not mean that I was contagious.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "I was not contagious, but I did have tuberculosis.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "And-- and-- and-- and for a while the sputum and the-- the-- the needle showed positive, et cetera.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] And when I came to Canada, I came to my aunt, who had one daughter.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "And her name is Elizabeth.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "And surprisingly enough, we were named after the same person.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "You see, I was Elsa, and she was Elizabeth.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "And she is-- I always say to her she's older than me, but she's two weeks-- two weeks older than me.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 36,
      "text": "So I always take great pride that Elizabeth is older than me.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 37,
      "text": "And we went to school together.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 38,
      "text": "I went in to York Memorial Collegiate, the one on-- on Keele.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 39,
      "text": "And I registered, and that's a story in itself that's a very interesting one.",
      "word_count": 14
    }
  ],
